<DocsLayout title="Customer History" section="CRM">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Access and manage all customer information in one place. Consolidating customer data
    allows you to review past work and make informed decisions for future projects.
  </p>
  <p>
    When a customer calls, having all their information at your fingertips makes it easy
    to find what you need and provide quick answers — like a central hub for each customer.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the <strong>Search box</strong> in the top left to find customers</li>
    <li>Click on a customer to view their complete profile</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Customer Profile</h2>
  <img src="/images/crm/customerhistory_01.png" alt="Customer Profile" />
  <p>All customer information is consolidated on one page:</p>

  <h3>Balance Due</h3>
  <p>View balance due information directly from QuickBooks Online.</p>

  <h3>Work Orders</h3>
  <p>Access both open and closed work orders directly from this screen.</p>

  <h3>Estimates</h3>
  <p>View open and closed estimates for the customer.</p>

  <h3>Equipment</h3>
  <p>See all equipment you service for this customer.</p>

  <h3>Recurrence Orders</h3>
  <p>View all recurring work orders associated with the customer.</p>

  <h3>Notes</h3>
  <p>Make notes and attach images at the customer profile level.</p>

  <h3>Payments</h3>
  <p>View all payments made by or to this customer.</p>

  <h3>Documents</h3>
  <p>
    Upload documents like contracts or building schematics. These documents are
    automatically included in work orders and viewable in the mobile app.
  </p>

  <h2>Mobile App Access</h2>
  <img src="/images/crm/customerhistory_02.png" alt="Mobile Customer History" />
  <p>
    Service providers can view customer history directly in the mobile app.
    Regardless of which technician previously worked with the customer, they can
    access past work history to better understand what was done.
  </p>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Customer data syncs two-way with QuickBooks — edit in either system</li>
    <li>All users can view customer information based on their access level</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Leverage customer profiles</strong> to quickly access past work information.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Add notes and documents</strong> to maintain comprehensive customer records.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Use the mobile app</strong> to review customer history before arriving on-site.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
